    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"876193\">Alyssa Rosenzweig</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Result.3A.3Ato_errno.20helper/near/512175578\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>While reviewing the DRM abstractions, I noticed a pattern:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">to_errno</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This seems to come up in other abstractions too. Time for a helper for this..?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>One small ergonomic painpoint is that <code>Result</code> comes from the stdlib, so we can't just define methods for it, we need an extension trait instead. So we could do:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IntoErrno</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">into_errno</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">i32</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IntoErrno</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">into_errno</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">i32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">to_errno</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"876193\">Alyssa Rosenzweig</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Result.3A.3Ato_errno.20helper/near/512176074\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This should compose with map as well, the DRM code on-list has</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">open</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">to_errno</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">driver_priv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">KBox</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">into_raw</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">into_inner_unchecked</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_raw</span><span class=\"p\">()).</span><span class=\"n\">driver_priv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">driver_priv</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cast</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which with this helper could instead be something like:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">open</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">drm</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">inspect</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">driver_priv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">KBox</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">into_raw</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">into_inner_unchecked</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_raw</span><span class=\"p\">()).</span><span class=\"n\">driver_priv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">driver_priv</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cast</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}).</span><span class=\"n\">to_errno</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>this will need <code>.map</code> instead of <code>.inspect</code>, since it consumes the value. But then it composes with the helper I defined above. (<code>.inspect</code> wouldn't work with the helper above, as that expects <code>()</code> in the <code>Ok(val)</code> variant).</p>",
